  <h1>Data Entry Jobs for Beginners</h1>

  <p>Data entry jobs are among the easiest non-technical jobs to start with. They require basic computer knowledge and attention to detail.</p>

  <h2>What is Data Entry?</h2>
  <p>Data entry involves entering, updating, or managing data in computer systems or databases.</p>

  <h2>Skills Required</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Typing speed and accuracy</li>
    <li>Basic computer knowledge</li>
    <li>Attention to detail</li>
    <li>Time management</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Types of Data Entry Jobs</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Online form filling</li>
    <li>Excel data entry</li>
    <li>Copy-paste work</li>
    <li>Database management</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Where to Find Jobs</h2>
  <p>Freelance websites, job portals, and company offices regularly hire data entry operators.</p>

